What is Quant?¶

"A quantitative analyst or, in financial jargon, a quant is a person who specializes in the application of mathematical and statistical methods – such as numerical or quantitative techniques – to financial and risk management problems."

--wikipedia

Not just in Finance

  • Sell side Quant (Goldman Sachs, JP Morgan, etc)

    • Pricing of financial instruments
    • PDE, stochastic processes, Black-Schole

  • Buy side Quant

    • Developing trading strategies
    • probability/statistics/machine learning/big data/...

Tips for quant interviews¶

  • Be honest about your resume
    • coursework
    • projects
  • Probability/statistics
  • Math vs Programming
    • Higher frequency more programming
  • Language: C++, Python**, R, Matlab

Susquehanna International Group¶
